Thursday September 5th 2013 11:52 pm -04:00,To arrange the IDLE Edit and Shell windows side by side in Microsoft Windows Vista or Windows 7 open them both right-click an empty area of the taskbar then click Show Windows Side by Side. The window thats currently selected or is otherwise in focus will be placed on the left and the other window will be placed on the right. When you do this only the two IDLE windows Edit and Shell may be open and not minimized; all other open windows must be minimized.Doing this may be second nature to many seasoned Windows users but it wasnt to me. I had to google how to do it. I found the Microsoft webpage titled Manage multiple windows. On Windows 7 this same side-by-side arrangement can be achieved using Snap. The webpage explains how to do this.Jim, Resolved,6
